1
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:02,435
He took her?

2
00:00:03,670 --> 00:00:04,771
He kidnapped her?

3
00:00:06,206 --> 00:00:07,374
She's not coming back?

4
00:00:08,308 --> 00:00:10,777
-No one said that!
-Oh, sorry.

5
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:12,979
I saw this letter.

6
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:17,851
"Hey Mom, I decided to travel a bit
with Fuga.

7
00:00:17,917 --> 00:00:19,886
Be well. I'll call you."

8
00:00:19,953 --> 00:00:22,655
This "Be well" seems to have
a deeper meaning.

9
00:00:22,722 --> 00:00:24,190
Don't say things like that!

10
00:00:24,257 --> 00:00:27,394
I don't know what to do
if she doesn't come home ever again.

11
00:00:27,460 --> 00:00:29,863
He's a phony.

12
00:00:29,929 --> 00:00:31,031
Or is he evil?

13
00:00:31,631 --> 00:00:34,300
That Fuga Ichinose, he's a crafty one!

14
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,469
It'll be fine.
She'll most likely come back.

15
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:40,073
What do you mean, "most likely"?
Not "certainly"?

16
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:41,841
Say certainly!

17
00:00:41,908 --> 00:00:43,176
Hello!

18
00:00:45,345 --> 00:00:46,746
I knew you were here.

19
00:00:47,747 --> 00:00:49,449
Hey, you!

20
00:00:49,516 --> 00:00:51,785
I have a souvenir from Okinawa.

21
00:00:52,485 --> 00:00:53,319
Okinawa?

22
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:54,788
You were in Okinawa, Sora?

23
00:00:54,854 --> 00:00:57,590
Okinawa donuts and a <i>shisa.</i>

24
00:00:58,124 --> 00:00:59,392
Mom, your souvenir is at home.

25
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:00,860
We're decorating now.

26
00:01:00,927 --> 00:01:03,530
Decorating? Who is?

27
00:01:12,505 --> 00:01:13,606
Looks pretty good.

28
00:01:13,673 --> 00:01:15,942
MAIN TITLE

29
00:01:17,210 --> 00:01:18,812
You were in Okinawa for all four days?

30
00:01:18,878 --> 00:01:21,014
Yes. We rode a hot air balloon.

31
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:24,050
Ichinose said there was a place
we could ride it in Okinawa.

32
00:01:25,885 --> 00:01:27,854
After that, we ate Okinawa soba.

33
00:01:28,555 --> 00:01:30,924
Why didn't you call me?

34
00:01:32,058 --> 00:01:34,761
I thought you'd tell me to come home.

35
00:01:37,197 --> 00:01:38,131
Mom,

36
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,233
you're still mad

37
00:01:40,733 --> 00:01:41,968
at Ichinose, right?

38
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:45,138
You were mad too.

39
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:49,042
But he's

40
00:01:50,009 --> 00:01:51,377
a little fun to be with.

41
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:55,482
Welcome home.

42
00:01:55,548 --> 00:01:57,550
We're home.

43
00:02:04,657 --> 00:02:06,159
Not bad!

44
00:02:06,226 --> 00:02:07,293
Right?

45
00:02:08,995 --> 00:02:09,896
Right?

46
00:02:11,731 --> 00:02:14,334
I don't really get it.

47
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,269
You'll start to get it.

48
00:02:16,336 --> 00:02:17,470
The beauty of driftwood.

49
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:21,074
I'll be on my way, then.
I don't want to interrupt

50
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,709
quality family time.

51
00:02:22,775 --> 00:02:24,911
-Where are you going?
-Home?

52
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:30,350
I found good lodgings.

53
00:02:31,084 --> 00:02:32,952
A toy store? The one in the corner?

54
00:02:33,019 --> 00:02:34,654
Across from the soba shop?

55
00:02:34,721 --> 00:02:35,588
Yeah.

56
00:02:36,422 --> 00:02:37,423
Do you know yo-yo?

57
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,893
Yo-yo? The toy?

58
00:02:40,393 --> 00:02:43,129
<i>He befriended Granny Obayashi with that.</i>

59
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:45,198
You're so good!

60
00:02:45,765 --> 00:02:47,834
Is this fine? It's not much.

61
00:02:48,401 --> 00:02:50,136
It's very nice.

62
00:02:51,137 --> 00:02:52,272
This is the ideal room.

63
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:53,439
Apparently, he was already

64
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:56,743
asked to do interiors for Taiyou-Do,
where Doctor Wataru works.

65
00:02:56,809 --> 00:02:59,546
<i>He was asked to decorate it</i>
<i>Asian style, with driftwood.</i>

66
00:02:59,612 --> 00:03:00,713
Wow!

67
00:03:01,447 --> 00:03:02,348
This is very nice!

68
00:03:02,415 --> 00:03:04,217
He even found a job.

69
00:03:04,284 --> 00:03:05,552
This soccer ball?

70
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:08,188
-Oh, let me help.
<i>-I'm sure his rent is super cheap.</i>

71
00:03:08,254 --> 00:03:09,088
It's 1,100 yen.

72
00:03:09,155 --> 00:03:12,292
He's got great survival
and communication skills.

73
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:14,160
Yeah. And then,

74
00:03:14,227 --> 00:03:16,930
<i>he got permission to park his car</i>
<i>inside Hikawa Shrine.</i>

75
00:03:16,996 --> 00:03:18,865
<i>He even sells driftwood there.</i>

76
00:03:18,932 --> 00:03:20,767
<i>And people buy it!</i>

77
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:24,037
I've never seen anyone like that.

78
00:03:24,103 --> 00:03:26,739
Even in Okinawa, he got stuff
for free from people!

79
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:28,241
That's what you noticed?

80
00:03:28,308 --> 00:03:30,143
He found a big job

81
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:32,212
to do the interiors
for a resort hotel there.

82
00:03:33,346 --> 00:03:35,148
He's very skilled at living life.

83
00:03:36,182 --> 00:03:37,850
I'm bad at stuff like that.

84
00:03:38,851 --> 00:03:40,787
Most kids these days are.

85
00:03:41,454 --> 00:03:43,289
You're a kid these days too!

86
00:03:43,356 --> 00:03:45,391
Oh, that's true, I am.

87
00:03:48,194 --> 00:03:49,095
I've never met

88
00:03:49,596 --> 00:03:51,564
someone that's

89
00:03:52,765 --> 00:03:53,900
quite like him.

90
00:03:54,634 --> 00:03:57,604
I think I should keep observing him.

91
00:03:59,505 --> 00:04:01,374
Not because he's your father?

92
00:04:02,709 --> 00:04:04,410
The fact that he's my father

93
00:04:04,477 --> 00:04:05,878
must have some meaning, right?

94
00:04:09,315 --> 00:04:10,450
I just thought

95
00:04:10,516 --> 00:04:12,819
you were very much Aoi Minase's daughter.

96
00:04:14,153 --> 00:04:15,922
Well, not by blood.

97
00:04:16,689 --> 00:04:17,890
What do you mean?

98
00:04:17,957 --> 00:04:20,093
You have a unique perspective on things.

99
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,095
Is it strange?

100
00:04:22,161 --> 00:04:24,864
No, it's a compliment.
I meant it as a compliment.

101
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:27,900
Hey, I'm really taking this to
Jump, alright?

102
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:29,902
Oh, in that case.

103
00:04:29,969 --> 00:04:33,506
Should we submit this
to a new talent contest?

104
00:04:33,573 --> 00:04:35,141
-New talent contest?
-It's this.

105
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:36,876
SUZURAN SHOPPING DISTRICT

106
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,978
MEN, WOMEN

107
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,048
Hello!

108
00:04:42,882 --> 00:04:44,584
Aoi. Long time no see.

109
00:04:46,919 --> 00:04:49,255
I couldn't write, so I came here
to feel refreshed.

110
00:04:49,322 --> 00:04:51,491
It felt so nice!

111
00:04:53,226 --> 00:04:54,427
Aoi.

112
00:04:55,395 --> 00:04:57,030
Aoi Minase.

113
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:01,834
Won't you come up?

114
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:08,141
Ms. Minase!

115
00:05:08,207 --> 00:05:11,077
Ms. Aoi!

116
00:05:11,711 --> 00:05:13,146
Stop it!

117
00:05:13,212 --> 00:05:14,747
Everyone's watching!

118
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,916
What? I can't hear.

119
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,853
Aoi!

120
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:23,222
OBAYASHI TOYS

121
00:05:26,726 --> 00:05:27,894
So you came.

122
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:35,635
This is Ryugu Sake, from Okinawa.

123
00:05:36,402 --> 00:05:37,236
You want some?

124
00:05:38,738 --> 00:05:40,306
What do you want from us?

125
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:45,278
You chased us all the way here,

126
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,713
and then you stayed.

127
00:05:48,081 --> 00:05:49,782
What do you want from us?

128
00:05:53,386 --> 00:05:54,787
What do you think?

129
00:05:57,323 --> 00:05:58,524
Hey, I made some

130
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:01,194
daikon radish and squid stew.

131
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:03,529
Please have some.

132
00:06:03,596 --> 00:06:05,665
Wow, it looks good!

133
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:09,569
Here.

134
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:12,638
-Chopsticks for you, Aoi.
-Oh, no, I…

135
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:14,607
I heard you know each other.

136
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:16,809
Aoi used to be

137
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,778
our customer back in the day.

138
00:06:19,445 --> 00:06:22,315
After that, it was Sora.

139
00:06:23,149 --> 00:06:24,417
-Join us, Kanae.
-What?

140
00:06:25,752 --> 00:06:28,588
I prefer to be alone.
I feel more relaxed that way.

141
00:06:28,654 --> 00:06:31,224
I'll eat this on my own while watching TV.

142
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:34,627
But Aoi, having him here with me,

143
00:06:34,694 --> 00:06:38,197
he's like a bodyguard. I feel so safe!

144
00:06:38,264 --> 00:06:39,966
I'll protect you from anything.

145
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,567
Including the bad men?

146
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:43,836
Because you're so beautiful.

147
00:06:46,139 --> 00:06:47,807
I didn't think my radishes

148
00:06:47,874 --> 00:06:50,610
would buy all this flattery!

149
00:06:52,044 --> 00:06:54,046
-It's true, you know!
-Alright.

150
00:06:55,948 --> 00:06:56,816
Right?

151
00:06:59,786 --> 00:07:01,921
The fact that Kanae of Obayashi Toys
is beautiful

152
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:04,323
has been said by everyone
in Suzuran District for many years.

153
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:06,292
You're beautiful too.

154
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,102
-It's good.
-Right?

155
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:18,438
This is

156
00:07:18,504 --> 00:07:20,406
a very rare sake.

157
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:23,876
They rest unprocessed awamori sake
for 20 years to get this aged sake.

158
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:25,978
They're very hard to come by.

159
00:07:29,415 --> 00:07:31,684
I'll have some of Kanae's radishes.

160
00:07:34,887 --> 00:07:35,988
Good, right?

161
00:07:38,524 --> 00:07:39,659
I'm going home soon.

162
00:07:41,527 --> 00:07:42,595
Oh!

163
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:45,131
RYUGU

164
00:07:45,198 --> 00:07:47,166
Want to play this?

165
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,569
Doing it alone is boring.

166
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:51,604
No, thank you.

167
00:07:56,409 --> 00:07:59,178
If I play this and win,

168
00:07:59,245 --> 00:08:01,113
will you go back to Ouse Island quickly?

169
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:02,281
I see.

170
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,984
Sure. I'm fine with that.

171
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:06,586
You promise?

172
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:08,020
Yes.

173
00:08:08,554 --> 00:08:10,356
Let's play.

174
00:08:35,548 --> 00:08:37,083
You're doing it again.

175
00:08:37,149 --> 00:08:40,119
You try to take the risky one
in the middle.

176
00:08:42,622 --> 00:08:43,890
You haven't changed.

177
00:08:52,598 --> 00:08:54,433
I won.

178
00:08:56,903 --> 00:08:59,071
I think I'll stay for a little longer.

179
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:02,909
Why?

180
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,679
Why did you lie about forgetting me?

181
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:10,016
Why did you lie?

182
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:18,624
I'm sorry.

183
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:25,464
When you came to see me…

184
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,700
Long time no see.

185
00:09:28,601 --> 00:09:29,769
It's me, Aoi.

186
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,005
<i>Sora's eyes</i>

187
00:09:33,606 --> 00:09:35,274
looked exactly like Suzu's.

188
00:09:37,543 --> 00:09:39,579
It was like Suzu was standing
right in front of me.

189
00:09:42,848 --> 00:09:45,818
I couldn't say that I remembered you.

190
00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:48,387
So I lied.

191
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:50,590
Also,

192
00:09:51,857 --> 00:09:54,260
I was hesitant because you came to see me

193
00:09:55,394 --> 00:09:56,562
so suddenly.

194
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,466
To be honest, I was shocked.

195
00:10:02,134 --> 00:10:03,269
I couldn't imagine

196
00:10:05,004 --> 00:10:06,305
that it was reality.

197
00:10:12,545 --> 00:10:13,813
I'm so sorry.

198
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:17,650
You supported Suzu.

199
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:21,454
And to think

200
00:10:23,255 --> 00:10:24,657
that you

201
00:10:25,324 --> 00:10:26,592
raised Suzu's child.

202
00:10:30,763 --> 00:10:31,998
We became

203
00:10:33,432 --> 00:10:35,001
best friends.

204
00:10:36,836 --> 00:10:37,670
What?

205
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,772
Suzu and me.

206
00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:43,709
Two women with the same scars.

207
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,080
We were two people

208
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:51,283
who couldn't forget you.

209
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:55,121
Yes, you were a terrible man.

210
00:10:56,756 --> 00:10:58,524
You had many other women.

211
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,962
Maybe to others,

212
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:06,198
you were a worthless shithead.

213
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,602
Yes. I was a worthless shithead.

214
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:12,371
But you had a charm that
surpassed the bad parts.

215
00:11:15,808 --> 00:11:17,877
Love can be like that, you know?

216
00:11:19,578 --> 00:11:21,981
Like, "Why do I even like someone
like this?"

217
00:11:24,116 --> 00:11:25,051
That's why

218
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:29,822
neither Suzu nor I

219
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:32,725
wanted to deny

220
00:11:33,392 --> 00:11:35,261
falling in love with you.

221
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,099
That's why Suzu

222
00:11:41,434 --> 00:11:43,202
decided to have Sora.

223
00:11:46,572 --> 00:11:47,506
I never said this

224
00:11:49,308 --> 00:11:51,143
to Suzu,

225
00:11:51,944 --> 00:11:53,179
but I always thought,

226
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:01,153
"Why does Suzu get to have your child,

227
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:07,393
and I can't?"

228
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:14,400
It was frustrating.

229
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:19,739
That's how much

230
00:12:21,474 --> 00:12:24,310
I loved you.

231
00:12:30,983 --> 00:12:33,385
Of course, it's all in the past.

232
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:39,458
But even so, I'm crying.

233
00:12:39,525 --> 00:12:41,360
It's very strange.

234
00:12:45,564 --> 00:12:46,398
But…

235
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:49,602
Why?

236
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,639
Why weren't you with her?

237
00:12:55,374 --> 00:12:58,577
Why didn't you stay with Suzu?

238
00:12:59,245 --> 00:13:01,580
Don't you know how scary it is

239
00:13:01,647 --> 00:13:04,550
for a woman to have a child all alone?

240
00:13:05,317 --> 00:13:06,952
And she was sick!

241
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:10,623
Fuga!

242
00:13:17,196 --> 00:13:19,098
Can I punch you?

243
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:24,637
Yes.

244
00:13:37,082 --> 00:13:38,784
That is for Suzu.

245
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:44,557
Um…

246
00:13:47,626 --> 00:13:48,594
I have a favor to ask.

247
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:53,833
You punched him?

248
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:55,134
More like a slap.

249
00:13:55,201 --> 00:13:56,335
My hand still hurts.

250
00:13:56,402 --> 00:13:58,103
Is Ichinose okay?

251
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,371
You're worried about him?

252
00:13:59,438 --> 00:14:01,674
Nah. But Ichinose didn't know

253
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:05,511
that Suzu was pregnant
with his kid, right?

254
00:14:05,578 --> 00:14:07,346
By kid, I mean me.

255
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:09,148
He didn't know.

256
00:14:09,215 --> 00:14:10,649
So it's not his fault.

257
00:14:11,217 --> 00:14:12,852
It is his fault!

258
00:14:12,918 --> 00:14:14,954
It's his fault for abandoning
his girlfriends!

259
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:17,356
But he remembered.

260
00:14:17,423 --> 00:14:19,825
Both you and Suzu, right?

261
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,028
He did remember.

262
00:14:24,263 --> 00:14:25,097
I'm glad.

263
00:14:26,098 --> 00:14:29,268
I'm glad he remembered my two moms.

264
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:33,906
Hey, you're too soft on Ichinose.

265
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:35,507
Did he brainwash you?

266
00:14:36,742 --> 00:14:37,710
His handsomeness

267
00:14:37,776 --> 00:14:40,045
reminds me of Itachi Uchiha from Naruto.

268
00:14:40,112 --> 00:14:41,146
It's too powerful.

269
00:14:42,748 --> 00:14:43,716
Mom.

270
00:14:44,316 --> 00:14:45,551
I want to go again.

271
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,289
If you, Ichinose, and I

272
00:14:50,356 --> 00:14:52,925
visited her all together,

273
00:14:52,992 --> 00:14:55,261
I'm sure Mother Suzu would feel relieved

274
00:14:55,928 --> 00:14:57,129
in heaven,

275
00:14:57,663 --> 00:14:58,797
up in the sky.

276
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:04,970
HOSHINO FAMILY

277
00:15:21,654 --> 00:15:23,422
The weather is nice.

278
00:15:23,489 --> 00:15:24,723
It's cold.

