That's all.

553
00:29:00,438 --> 00:29:02,240
I guess I'm a little sad.

554
00:29:03,942 --> 00:29:05,510
But maybe Suzu

555
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:08,012
didn't want to tell me.

556
00:29:21,059 --> 00:29:21,993
She probably thought

557
00:29:22,494 --> 00:29:24,662
if she told you, you would go away.

558
00:29:24,729 --> 00:29:26,264
What? Why?

559
00:29:26,331 --> 00:29:27,866
Because he didn't write

560
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:30,068
a letter to you.

561
00:29:30,135 --> 00:29:31,169
But he wrote to Suzu.

562
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:34,339
It means he loved Suzu more.

563
00:29:34,405 --> 00:29:36,441
You hit me right where it hurts!

564
00:29:36,508 --> 00:29:37,709
Sorry.

565
00:29:39,043 --> 00:29:41,746
But maybe if she told you, you could've

566
00:29:41,813 --> 00:29:42,947
gotten mad

567
00:29:43,481 --> 00:29:44,415
or jealous,

568
00:29:45,350 --> 00:29:46,718
and felt bad

569
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:48,486
and have gone away.

570
00:29:49,020 --> 00:29:51,456
You might have told her to go and

571
00:29:51,523 --> 00:29:52,557
be with Ichinose.

572
00:29:52,624 --> 00:29:55,026
I probably would've said that.

573
00:29:55,693 --> 00:29:57,262
I don't know about

574
00:29:57,328 --> 00:29:59,130
jealousy or anger,

575
00:29:59,764 --> 00:30:03,568
but I would've thought it's better
to be raised by your real mom and dad.

576
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:05,970
But Suzu didn't think so.

577
00:30:07,438 --> 00:30:08,606
Rather than being raised by

578
00:30:08,673 --> 00:30:10,975
the mysterious Ichinose with many women,

579
00:30:11,042 --> 00:30:13,745
she thought it was better
if I was raised by you.

580
00:30:14,612 --> 00:30:15,780
If she ever died.

581
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:28,927
She trusted me like that,

582
00:30:30,361 --> 00:30:34,199
but was I able to raise you properly?

583
00:30:37,802 --> 00:30:40,839
I'll prove it.

584
00:30:40,905 --> 00:30:43,441
I'm a pretty good kid, aren't I?

585
00:31:02,393 --> 00:31:03,528
Long time no see.

586
00:31:06,664 --> 00:31:07,732
It's been a while.

587
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:10,001
What is it?

588
00:31:10,068 --> 00:31:12,337
You look as if you've seen a ghost.

589
00:31:12,403 --> 00:31:14,239
Look, I have legs.

590
00:31:18,276 --> 00:31:19,244
Why did you

591
00:31:20,311 --> 00:31:21,446
lie to me?

592
00:31:22,113 --> 00:31:23,414
Hey.

593
00:31:23,481 --> 00:31:25,583
That's the first thing you say to me?

594
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:30,822
I'm sorry.

595
00:31:32,557 --> 00:31:33,691
I'm really…

596
00:31:34,525 --> 00:31:35,426
sorry.

597
00:31:36,861 --> 00:31:37,795
I lied?

598
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:40,665
Oh, about that?

599
00:31:41,666 --> 00:31:44,335
I should be allowed to say
I have a new man, don't you think?

600
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:48,773
You really mistreated me, you know?

601
00:31:50,842 --> 00:31:53,711
I told you I had Sora
because I wanted to be a good mom.

602
00:31:54,946 --> 00:31:57,749
It was the pride of a woman.

603
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:00,585
"I left your child

604
00:32:00,652 --> 00:32:04,022
in this world before I went."
It was my statement.

605
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:07,158
Why didn't you get back with me then?

606
00:32:08,192 --> 00:32:11,296
Because I couldn't trust you.

607
00:32:13,431 --> 00:32:14,332
But

608
00:32:15,233 --> 00:32:17,101
I'm glad you're doing well.

609
00:32:20,204 --> 00:32:21,205
You too, Suzu.

610
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:23,841
Hey.

611
00:32:24,609 --> 00:32:26,611
I can't reach down from

612
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:28,479
up above the clouds very well.

613
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:30,882
Take care of stuff

614
00:32:31,749 --> 00:32:32,750
in this world, alright?

615
00:32:36,454 --> 00:32:37,322
Promise me.

616
00:32:43,861 --> 00:32:44,896
ODAYA

617
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:46,164
What I'm saying is,

618
00:32:47,398 --> 00:32:49,400
because Mom is too giving

619
00:32:50,868 --> 00:32:51,936
and kind,

620
00:32:53,571 --> 00:32:54,872
I'm worried that…

621
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:57,875
What is it?

622
00:33:00,411 --> 00:33:01,679
Maybe Mom

623
00:33:01,746 --> 00:33:02,847
gave up on marriage

624
00:33:03,381 --> 00:33:06,017
for my sake.

625
00:33:06,617 --> 00:33:08,353
Maybe she gave up on having

626
00:33:08,419 --> 00:33:09,620
her own kids for me.

627
00:33:09,687 --> 00:33:13,091
You don't get it, do you?
She's not the type!

628
00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:14,492
Actually,

629
00:33:15,226 --> 00:33:16,728
could she think like that?

630
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:18,563
Hey,

631
00:33:18,629 --> 00:33:22,333
you left for France
a year after Sora was born.

632
00:33:23,034 --> 00:33:25,303
I was observing Aoi from here

633
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:27,271
for all these years.

634
00:33:28,172 --> 00:33:29,741
So let me say this.

635
00:33:30,408 --> 00:33:32,343
Sora.

636
00:33:32,410 --> 00:33:33,444
I'd say,

637
00:33:34,045 --> 00:33:37,715
your concerns are groundless.

638
00:33:37,782 --> 00:33:39,150
You're worried over nothing.

639
00:33:40,418 --> 00:33:41,853
Aoi, with her beauty,

640
00:33:41,919 --> 00:33:43,755
was always popular with boys.

641
00:33:43,821 --> 00:33:45,323
And Sora, you were so cute too.

642
00:33:45,390 --> 00:33:47,291
Aoi would tell them,

643
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:48,960
"If you marry me,

644
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:51,529
you get to be with
this very cute girl too!

645
00:33:52,263 --> 00:33:54,165
It's like getting both

646
00:33:54,232 --> 00:33:57,668
a diamond and an emerald!

647
00:33:57,735 --> 00:33:59,537
Aren't you so lucky?"

648
00:33:59,604 --> 00:34:01,005
She said that all the time.

649
00:34:01,773 --> 00:34:02,840
She's strong!

650
00:34:02,907 --> 00:34:05,910
Whether they were doctors or bureaucrats,

651
00:34:05,977 --> 00:34:07,612
all the men

652
00:34:08,146 --> 00:34:09,313
were after her.

653
00:34:10,114 --> 00:34:13,384
Stories like that about Aoi
always piss me off!

654
00:34:13,951 --> 00:34:16,054
Gon-chan, are we talking about that now?

655
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,288
We're talking about me.

656
00:34:18,689 --> 00:34:19,524
Sorry.

657
00:34:19,590 --> 00:34:22,393
There's nothing for you to be
concerned about, Sora.

658
00:34:22,460 --> 00:34:23,961
Aoi just felt

659
00:34:24,028 --> 00:34:26,397
more at home
staying with just the two of you,

660
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:28,266
Sora.

661
00:34:28,332 --> 00:34:30,068
That's why she didn't marry.

662
00:34:30,701 --> 00:34:32,070
That's all.

663
00:34:32,136 --> 00:34:33,738
Can I ask you something else?

664
00:34:33,805 --> 00:34:35,873
Hey, ask me something too.

665
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:38,276
One question remains.

666
00:34:39,177 --> 00:34:41,012
Why did Mother Suzu,

667
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:43,081
Suzu, who passed away,

668
00:34:43,147 --> 00:34:44,482
let Fuga Ichinose know

669
00:34:44,549 --> 00:34:46,984
that I existed, in her letter?

670
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:49,253
If she didn't want to

671
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:51,456
be in the way of an up and coming star,

672
00:34:51,522 --> 00:34:53,724
she should have kept quiet about me.

673
00:34:55,993 --> 00:34:59,097
I think that Suzu, before she died,
wanted to leave you with

674
00:34:59,997 --> 00:35:01,532
another person to depend on

675
00:35:01,599 --> 00:35:04,502
in case something happened to Aoi.

676
00:35:06,571 --> 00:35:08,940
It's much easier on children if they have

677
00:35:09,006 --> 00:35:11,075
two parents instead of just one.

678
00:35:11,709 --> 00:35:13,744
It's better to have more people
to protect you.

679
00:35:14,612 --> 00:35:15,780
That's why I think

680
00:35:15,847 --> 00:35:17,582
she told Fuga Ichinose

681
00:35:17,648 --> 00:35:20,618
that he had a daughter.

682
00:35:22,386 --> 00:35:23,321
That's my opinion.

683
00:35:24,088 --> 00:35:25,857
He might be

684
00:35:25,923 --> 00:35:29,026
some kind of help to you in the future
when you need him.

685
00:35:31,729 --> 00:35:32,697
Please…

686
00:35:33,464 --> 00:35:34,432
don't tell

687
00:35:34,932 --> 00:35:36,267
Mom about that, okay?

688
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:37,969
Sora.

689
00:35:39,370 --> 00:35:41,405
I'm sure Aoi knows.

690
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:49,080
We've received great feedback
for <i>Midsummer Skies are Dreams.</i>

691
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:50,581
The reader survey is good too.

692
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:54,318
Sure, the survey is fine.

693
00:35:54,819 --> 00:35:56,888
Huh? What's wrong?

694
00:35:57,388 --> 00:35:58,789
<i>Why do you ask?</i>

695
00:35:59,323 --> 00:36:00,992
Your tone is gloomy.

696
00:36:01,058 --> 00:36:02,693
It's very obvious.

697
00:36:03,528 --> 00:36:05,096
Hold on. Could it be…?

698
00:36:06,030 --> 00:36:07,498
I checked online.

699
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:10,034
<i>I told you not to do that!</i>

700
00:36:10,601 --> 00:36:12,036
Stop Googling yourself!

701
00:36:12,103 --> 00:36:13,671
You know, the thing is,

702
00:36:13,738 --> 00:36:16,107
even after reading 100 good comments,

703
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:18,643
if I find one criticism,
that's all I think about!

704
00:36:19,377 --> 00:36:20,711
What did it say?

705
00:36:20,778 --> 00:36:23,347
That I'm behind the times.

706
00:36:23,915 --> 00:36:24,982
Ms. Aoi.

707
00:36:26,250 --> 00:36:27,685
At one time,

708
00:36:27,752 --> 00:36:29,453
you released several

709
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:32,190
explosive hit books that sold over
a million copies.

710
00:36:33,224 --> 00:36:35,159
Like <i>The Scent of the Sky</i>

711
00:36:35,226 --> 00:36:36,427
and <i>The Tears About to Fall.</i>

712
00:36:36,994 --> 00:36:38,629
That's true.

713
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:39,530
<i>Ms. Aoi.</i>

714
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:42,833
Only writers who survive

715
00:36:42,900 --> 00:36:45,770
for an era and leave
a strong impression on the public

716
00:36:45,836 --> 00:36:47,705
get to be "behind the times."

717
00:36:49,473 --> 00:36:52,176
The only way you can tell if an author
is truly behind the times

718
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:55,780
is if she's able to continue writing
fresh work right now.

719
00:36:56,414 --> 00:36:57,381
That's what I believe.

720
00:36:59,417 --> 00:37:01,786
<i>Ms. Aoi, you haven't retired,</i>

721
00:37:01,852 --> 00:37:03,321
<i>and you still feel strongly.</i>

722
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:04,989
And, you've got energy.

723
00:37:06,791 --> 00:37:08,259
Watching you like that,

724
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:11,495
I start thinking that the times will
end up

725
00:37:12,463 --> 00:37:13,631
being behind you.

726
00:37:16,133 --> 00:37:18,636
I'm so glad you're my editor, Soseki.

727
00:37:20,104 --> 00:37:22,273
-About that…
<i>-Sorry!</i>

728
00:37:23,074 --> 00:37:25,810
A three-star restaurant just
opened a bakery in Suzuran District.

729
00:37:25,876 --> 00:37:29,714
They serve fresh-baked cream bread
at five o'clock!

730
00:37:30,481 --> 00:37:31,616
So, I gotta go!

731
00:37:35,319 --> 00:37:37,955
Bread comes before me, huh?

732
00:37:38,489 --> 00:37:41,092
<i>UMBILICAL CORD,</i> AOI MINASE

733
00:37:41,659 --> 00:37:42,493
I see.

734
00:37:43,094 --> 00:37:45,229
You went with Ichinose and your mother

735
00:37:45,296 --> 00:37:47,632
to visit your birth mother's grave?

736
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:51,335
I'm glad we did it.

737
00:37:56,207 --> 00:37:57,241
Hey.

738
00:37:58,576 --> 00:37:59,944
I asked Ichinose

739
00:38:01,112 --> 00:38:02,613
to do the Taiyou-Do interiors

740
00:38:03,848 --> 00:38:04,749
on purpose.

741
00:38:06,484 --> 00:38:07,985
So that Ichinose could

742
00:38:08,052 --> 00:38:09,553
stay in Suzuran.

743
00:38:10,988 --> 00:38:11,822
Why?

744
00:38:12,456 --> 00:38:13,624
So that he could spend

745
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:16,160
more time with you.

746
00:38:19,196 --> 00:38:20,231
I lost my parents

747
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:23,634
when I was young

748
00:38:24,235 --> 00:38:25,836
and I had many regrets.

749
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:29,774
I've always wished I could
talk to them more.

750
00:38:32,143 --> 00:38:33,210
So I thought

751
00:38:34,512 --> 00:38:37,882
you would think the same thing
if Ichinose left.

752
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:40,384
You got a great opportunity.

753
00:38:41,218 --> 00:38:43,287
So I wanted to give you more time
to be together.

754
00:38:45,589 --> 00:38:46,857
Doctor Wataru…

755
00:38:48,025 --> 00:38:50,561
Mana, you don't have a Switch!

756
00:38:50,628 --> 00:38:51,462
Yeah.

757
00:38:51,529 --> 00:38:53,731
You can't play if you don't have a Switch.

758
00:38:53,798 --> 00:38:55,766
-You can't join us!
-Bye!

759
00:39:55,192 --> 00:39:56,827
<i>The Fourth World from the Right.</i>

760
00:39:57,461 --> 00:39:59,296
-For the title?
-Yeah.

761
00:40:00,264 --> 00:40:02,166
It means the world I live in

762
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:05,102
is just one out of

763
00:40:05,169 --> 00:40:06,036
many worlds.

764
00:40:09,106 --> 00:40:10,541
It doesn't feel very Jump.

765
00:40:11,375 --> 00:40:13,010
-That's true.
-Yeah.

766
00:40:13,077 --> 00:40:15,346
-I got it. I'll think about it more.
-Okay.

767
00:40:16,380 --> 00:40:17,615
Hey.

768
00:40:17,681 --> 00:40:19,183
About this panel…

769
00:40:20,651 --> 00:40:23,454
Your drawing sucks.
I have no idea what this is!

770
00:40:25,289 --> 00:40:26,123
Sorry.

771
00:40:26,690 --> 00:40:28,526
Hey, don't apologize!

772
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:31,529
Otherwise, I'm just a mean girl.

773
00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:33,297
You're right.

774
00:40:33,898 --> 00:40:35,633
Hey, to change the subject,

775
00:40:35,699 --> 00:40:37,034
are you hungry?

776
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:40,137
-I am!
-Alright.

777
00:40:43,340 --> 00:40:44,842
Ichinose!

778
00:40:45,376 --> 00:40:46,844
Your timer was beeping so I turned it off.

779
00:40:46,911 --> 00:40:48,446
Oh, thank you.

780
00:40:50,047 --> 00:40:52,049
I was making <i>rafute</i>

781
00:40:52,116 --> 00:40:53,317
with the <i>awamori.</i>

782
00:40:53,951 --> 00:40:56,187
We were making Okinawa food together.

783
00:40:56,253 --> 00:40:58,656
-Join us, Aoi.
-But I have this.

784
00:40:59,523 --> 00:41:02,126
Oh, that's the popular bakery!

785
00:41:02,193 --> 00:41:04,495
Next to Café Tomoshibi, right?

786
00:41:04,562 --> 00:41:05,863
-Exactly!
-Wow!

787
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:07,731
Save that

788
00:41:07,798 --> 00:41:09,500
for tomorrow's breakfast.

789
00:41:09,567 --> 00:41:11,802
Did you hear that, Aoi? So come over!

790
00:41:19,310 --> 00:41:20,644
So delicious!

791
00:41:21,579 --> 00:41:22,413
I'm glad.

792
00:41:22,913 --> 00:41:25,516
You were always a good cook.

793
00:41:26,317 --> 00:41:28,953
You could only boil water.

794
00:41:29,620 --> 00:41:32,056
How did you date a girl like me?

795
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:34,258
Even though I thought you forgot about me.

796
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,260
No.

797
00:41:37,361 --> 00:41:38,629
You were like

798
00:41:39,430 --> 00:41:40,731
a sunflower.

799
00:41:42,199 --> 00:41:43,567
A sunflower in the summer.

800
00:41:46,403 --> 00:41:47,972
I was always

801
00:41:48,038 --> 00:41:49,673
a heavy and gloomy person.

802
00:41:50,207 --> 00:41:52,176
I was the type to do
underground theater in Shimokita.

803
00:41:54,378 --> 00:41:58,182
If I was an unpopular literary magazine
with a thick letterpress,

804
00:41:58,949 --> 00:42:00,918
the one week I spent with you

805
00:42:01,552 --> 00:42:04,288
is the color-print page of my life.

806
00:42:05,823 --> 00:42:07,024
A color-printed pinup girl?

807
00:42:07,091 --> 00:42:08,158
Exactly.

808
00:42:09,593 --> 00:42:12,530
But you'd get tired if the whole book
was printed in color.

809
00:42:12,596 --> 00:42:13,797
You can't relax.

810
00:42:18,068 --> 00:42:19,403
Want to play Jenga?

811
00:42:19,470 --> 00:42:21,205
Great idea!

812
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:23,340
What should we bet on?

813
00:42:24,942 --> 00:42:27,978
Let me think.

814
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:36,620
<i>The Scent</i>

815
00:42:37,454 --> 00:42:38,722
<i>of the Sky.</i>

816
00:42:47,331 --> 00:42:48,532
<i>We Can Meet Again.</i>

817
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:50,601
<i>Tomorrow.</i>

818
00:42:53,003 --> 00:42:53,938
What is it?

819
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:05,115
<i>An Off-Handed Goodbye.</i>

820
00:43:07,818 --> 00:43:09,720
<i>Crybaby</i>

821
00:43:10,321 --> 00:43:11,155
<i>Evening.</i>

822
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:17,261
I read

823
00:43:17,828 --> 00:43:19,430
all of your books.

824
00:43:20,531 --> 00:43:21,765
They were all beautiful.

825
00:43:27,371 --> 00:43:28,472
I fell in love

826
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:32,076
with many people after that.

827
00:43:34,778 --> 00:43:36,780
After we broke up.

828
00:43:40,951 --> 00:43:42,386
But

829
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,556
I couldn't truly love anyone else.

830
00:43:48,892 --> 00:43:50,961
On stage

831
00:43:51,028 --> 00:43:52,730
you were so beautiful,

832
00:43:53,564 --> 00:43:55,299
and off the stage

833
00:43:56,467 --> 00:43:57,835
you were very loveable.

834
00:43:59,069 --> 00:44:00,571
Now,

835
00:44:01,105 --> 00:44:02,673
I'm just some driftwood seller.

836
00:44:04,775 --> 00:44:07,277
But you haven't changed.

837
00:44:09,079 --> 00:44:10,781
You're the only you

838
00:44:11,315 --> 00:44:13,017
in this whole entire world.

839
00:44:19,890 --> 00:44:21,325
I'll take the smaller one.

840
00:44:21,825 --> 00:44:22,826
-Really?
-Yeah.

841
00:44:27,631 --> 00:44:28,465
So good!

842
00:44:30,434 --> 00:44:31,802
Hey.

843
00:44:31,869 --> 00:44:33,037
-Drink it!
-I can't.

844
00:44:33,604 --> 00:44:35,639
How nice!

845
00:44:35,706 --> 00:44:36,974
You're doing it

846
00:44:37,041 --> 00:44:38,876
later tonight, right?

847
00:44:40,077 --> 00:44:41,378
Stop it!

848
00:44:42,680 --> 00:44:45,015
Hey, she's pretty cute!

849
00:44:45,082 --> 00:44:46,717
Let me touch you!

850
00:44:46,784 --> 00:44:48,352
-Don't touch her!
-What the hell?

851
00:44:48,419 --> 00:44:50,154
Hey, stop! Stop!

852
00:44:50,220 --> 00:44:51,088
Shut up!

853
00:44:54,958 --> 00:44:56,393
Hey!

854
00:44:56,460 --> 00:44:57,695
-Hey!
-Stop it!

855
00:44:57,761 --> 00:44:59,096
What are you guys doing!

856
00:44:59,830 --> 00:45:01,331
I'll call the police.

857
00:45:01,398 --> 00:45:02,533
Shit.

858
00:45:03,267 --> 00:45:04,101
This is bad.

859
00:45:05,869 --> 00:45:06,837
You okay?

860
00:45:06,904 --> 00:45:08,706
-Are you alright?
-Yes.

861
00:45:08,772 --> 00:45:11,475
They're just some brats that are
always loitering around here.

862
00:45:12,476 --> 00:45:14,011
Go home!

863
00:45:16,447 --> 00:45:18,048
This area isn't safe.

864
00:45:18,115 --> 00:45:20,484
It's not like where you live.

865
00:45:21,952 --> 00:45:23,387
My glasses.

866
00:45:24,988 --> 00:45:26,223
Where are my glasses?

867
00:45:33,997 --> 00:45:36,233
They're cracked. The frames too.

868
00:45:38,268 --> 00:45:39,737
I'm really nearsighted.

869
00:45:40,237 --> 00:45:41,538
I can't see without them.

870
00:45:44,374 --> 00:45:46,110
I'll put these away. Do you have spares?

871
00:45:47,377 --> 00:45:49,279
I have a spare pair at home.

872
00:45:50,047 --> 00:45:52,483
I'll head home for now.

873
00:45:55,486 --> 00:45:57,588
I'll walk you home.

874
00:46:02,292 --> 00:46:03,494
So you don't fall.

875
00:46:05,395 --> 00:46:06,230
Okay.

876
00:46:13,904 --> 00:46:15,072
Hey.

877
00:46:15,839 --> 00:46:16,740
What is it?

878
00:46:17,374 --> 00:46:18,542
I thought only

879
00:46:19,109 --> 00:46:22,446
boyfriends and girlfriends held hands.

880
00:46:26,984 --> 00:46:28,752
It's because it's an emergency.

881
00:46:29,887 --> 00:46:31,221
Your glasses are broken.

882
00:46:32,723 --> 00:46:33,690
I see.

883
00:46:41,665 --> 00:46:43,367
Hey, it's red.

884
00:46:43,433 --> 00:46:44,401
I can see that.

885
00:46:45,068 --> 00:46:46,303
It's just blurry.

886
00:46:49,373 --> 00:46:50,541
You don't wear contacts?

887
00:46:51,175 --> 00:46:52,543
I'm scared to put them in my eyes.

888
00:46:52,609 --> 00:46:54,578
That's true.

889
00:47:08,358 --> 00:47:09,960
It's snowing!

890
00:47:13,797 --> 00:47:14,932
It's beautiful.

891
00:47:16,233 --> 00:47:18,702
I wonder if Sora's seeing
this snow right now.

892
00:47:22,506 --> 00:47:23,574
Aoi.

893
00:47:26,944 --> 00:47:29,179
What if we…

894
00:47:32,115 --> 00:47:33,250
got together again?

895
00:47:34,818 --> 00:47:35,652
What?

896
00:47:37,221 --> 00:47:38,455
Or rather,

897
00:47:39,690 --> 00:47:41,291
start together again?

898
00:47:48,432 --> 00:47:49,399
What are you doing?

899
00:47:50,534 --> 00:47:52,202
<i>The Scent of the Snow.</i>

900
00:47:52,870 --> 00:47:55,339
Oh, your mom's novel!

901
00:47:56,273 --> 00:47:58,242
<i>The Scent of the Sky.</i>

902
00:48:01,745 --> 00:48:03,714
It does smell like snow!

903
00:48:04,381 --> 00:48:06,550
What kind of smell is it?

904
00:48:06,617 --> 00:48:09,119
Doesn't it smell like mints?

905
00:48:11,021 --> 00:48:12,222
It stings.

906
00:48:14,224 --> 00:48:15,425
It's green. We can cross.

907
00:48:16,393 --> 00:48:18,629
Even though no one's here.

908
00:48:20,664 --> 00:48:21,899
One day…

909
00:48:25,636 --> 00:48:27,004
One day, in the future.

910
00:48:29,539 --> 00:48:31,708
We're sophomores in college now.

911
00:48:33,577 --> 00:48:35,545
We'll become juniors in April.

912
00:48:36,847 --> 00:48:38,448
We'll start looking for jobs.

913
00:48:39,449 --> 00:48:40,450
And we won't draw manga.

914
00:48:40,517 --> 00:48:43,620
Don't talk about that when we're about to

915
00:48:43,687 --> 00:48:44,821
submit to Jump!

916
00:48:44,888 --> 00:48:46,390
I know.

917
00:48:47,291 --> 00:48:48,358
That's why

918
00:48:49,726 --> 00:48:50,961
this is all theoretical.

919
00:48:51,862 --> 00:48:55,232
A story about
the third world from the right.

920
00:49:02,406 --> 00:49:03,874
Then, we'll graduate college,

921
00:49:04,474 --> 00:49:06,777
we'll become adults,

922
00:49:07,911 --> 00:49:09,379
and start working.

923
00:49:11,014 --> 00:49:12,716
We won't draw manga,

924
00:49:13,350 --> 00:49:14,651
and when something happens,

925
00:49:14,718 --> 00:49:17,854
I won't call you
and ask you to help me.

926
00:49:19,623 --> 00:49:20,657
That will all

927
00:49:21,391 --> 00:49:22,359
go away.

928
00:49:23,260 --> 00:49:25,062
That's not true.

929
00:49:25,128 --> 00:49:26,196
Nothing will change.

930
00:49:27,297 --> 00:49:28,432
It will change!

931
00:49:32,002 --> 00:49:33,170
Not everything

932
00:49:35,038 --> 00:49:36,306
will change.

933
00:49:49,686 --> 00:49:50,654
What is it?

934
00:49:56,026 --> 00:49:58,028
The Scent of Hikaru.

935
00:49:59,396 --> 00:50:00,797
What the hell is that?

936
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:04,801
Do I stink? Am I okay?

937
00:50:06,803 --> 00:50:08,438
You smell like grass.

938
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:11,641
Like my childhood.

939
00:50:14,378 --> 00:50:16,213
How romantic!

940
00:50:17,581 --> 00:50:18,849
I'll remember

941
00:50:20,250 --> 00:50:21,351
this smell, always.

942
00:50:32,929 --> 00:50:34,197
<i>One day,</i>

943
00:50:34,731 --> 00:50:36,500
<i>I'll remember this day,</i>

944
00:50:36,566 --> 00:50:38,468
<i>I'll remember this moment,</i>

945
00:50:39,369 --> 00:50:41,304
<i>and think back on it longingly.</i>

946
00:50:42,406 --> 00:50:43,740
<i>That's what I think now.</i>

947
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:47,411
<i>Even after</i>

948
00:50:47,477 --> 00:50:49,179
<i>the light turned green,</i>

949
00:50:49,813 --> 00:50:51,348
<i>we couldn't start walking.</i>

950
00:50:53,583 --> 00:50:55,118
THE FINAL EPISODE

951
00:50:55,185 --> 00:50:57,487
-Won't you go to New York with me?
-What?

952
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:59,456
I just cast a spell on you.

953
00:50:59,523 --> 00:51:00,557
<i>All the men want Mom!</i>

954
00:51:00,624 --> 00:51:01,858
<i>She might go away.</i>

955
00:51:01,925 --> 00:51:03,794
<i>Even if your mom goes to</i>
<i>Okinawa, I'm right here.</i>

956
00:51:03,860 --> 00:51:05,896
<i>Get out! Get out of this town!</i>

957
00:51:05,962 --> 00:51:07,964
<i>I'll decide where to go myself!</i>

958
